quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,1,"All praise be to Allah Who created the heavens and earth, and made darkness and light; yet those who disbelieve set up equals to their Lord.",""
  6,2,"It is He Who created you from clay, then decreed a term [for your life], and another term [for resurrection] known only to Him – yet you still doubt.",""
  6,3,"He is Allah in the heavens and on earth<sup>1</sup>. He knows your secrets and what you reveal, and knows whatever you earn.","[1] Who is rightfully worshiped by the dwellers of these two realms."
  6,4,"No sign ever comes to them from their Lord except that they turn away from it.",""
  6,5,"They rejected the truth when it came to them, but soon they will face the consequences of what they used to ridicule.",""
  6,6,"Have they not seen how many generations We destroyed before them? We had made them more powerful in the land than We have made you. We sent down for them abundant rain and made rivers flow beneath them. Yet We destroyed them for their sins and brought forth after them other generations.",""
  6,7,"Even if We had sent down to you [O Prophet] a revelation written on paper, and they were to touch it with their hands, the disbelievers would still have said, “This is nothing but clear magic!”",""
  6,8,"They say: Why has no angel been sent down to him<sup>2</sup>? If We did send down an angel, the matter would have been decided and then they would not be given any respite.","[2] Testifying for his prophethood (ﷺ)."
